(1) Warning devices:
(a) Are missing, do not function as designed or are not of an approved type;
(b) Are improperly stored;
(c) Are not readily accessible.

(2) Signs or lettering:
(a) When required, are missing, illegible or obscured;
(b) Are not proper size or color;
(c) Are not located as required or permitted.

(3) Retro-reflective tape:
(a) Is missing when required, or is loose, defective, or obscured;
(b) Is not the proper size or color;
(c) Is not located as required.

(4) Identification:
